data.meta_description: GIMP ppt - Free download as (.odp), PDF File (.pdf), Text File (.txt) or view presentation slides online. Gimp is a free and open-source raster graphics editor developed in 1995 as a semester-long student project. It was originally called the Image Manipulation Program but later became part of the GNU project and was renamed GNU Image Manipulation Program. Gimp has been continuously developed and updated since its initial release, with major new features and improvements added in each version. It is compatible with Linux, Windows, and macOS and provides tools for image editing, retouching, and manipulation.
